# =============================================================================
# PostgreSQL — Prisma requires TWO URLs for pooled hosts (Neon on Vercel, etc.)
# =============================================================================
# - DATABASE_URL          → app queries (often pooled / PgBouncer)
# - DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED → migrations (`prisma migrate deploy` in `npm run build`)
#
# Local Docker / embedded Postgres: use the SAME connection string for both.

# --- Local / Docker (port 5432)
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:postgres@127.0.0.1:5432/ankiicu"
# DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED="postgresql://postgres:postgres@127.0.0.1:5432/ankiicu"

# --- Embedded Postgres — npm run dev:local (port 5433)
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:postgres@127.0.0.1:5433/ankiicu"
# DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED="postgresql://postgres:postgres@127.0.0.1:5433/ankiicu"

# =============================================================================
# Vercel — Postgres via Marketplace (Neon)
# =============================================================================
# "Vercel Postgres" was retired; new databases use Neon:
#   https://vercel.com/marketplace/neon
#
# 1. Vercel Dashboard → Storage → Neon → Create / Connect.
# 2. Connect your **AnkiICU** project (Production + Preview as needed).
# 3. The integration injects at least:
#      DATABASE_URL              (pooled)
#      DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED     (direct — required for Prisma migrations)
# 4. Deploy: `npm run build` already runs `prisma migrate deploy`, which creates
#    every table needed for upload + generation:
#      SourceFile, GenerationProgress, AnkiCard, GenerationJob, User
# 5. Optional Preview Branching: enable in the integration so each preview gets
#    its own DB branch; keep migrations in the build so schema matches code.
#
# If you only see one URL in the UI, copy the "direct" / "unpooled" string into
# DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED and keep the pooled string in DATABASE_URL.

# =============================================================================
# Prisma Postgres (prisma.io) — pooled + direct from Console
# =============================================================================
# DATABASE_URL="postgres://USER:PASSWORD@pooled.db.prisma.io:5432/postgres?sslmode=require"
# DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED="postgres://USER:PASSWORD@db.prisma.io:5432/postgres?sslmode=require"

# =============================================================================
# Vercel-native Prisma Postgres integration (alternative)
# =============================================================================
# npx vercel integration add prisma/prisma-postgres
# Map injected vars to DATABASE_URL + DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED if names differ.

# One-command trial DB (24h): npm run db:prisma-create

# Optional API gate (production): /login — set APP_API_SECRET or use Bearer token
# APP_API_SECRET="generate-a-long-random-string"

# Optional max upload bytes (default ~4 MiB on Vercel, 15 MiB self-hosted)
# MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES=15728640

# DEBUG_AI=

# --- OpenAI (card generation). Optional if users enter a key in the browser.
# OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-..."
# OPENAI_BASE_URL="https://api.openai.com/v1"
# OPENAI_MODEL="gpt-4o-mini"
